<div class="theorem" id="theorem-CLTLT" acro="CLTLT" titletext="Composition of Linear Transformations is a Linear Transformation">
<h5 class="theorem">
<span class="type">Theorem </span><span class="acro">CLTLT</span><span class="titletext"> Composition of Linear Transformations is a Linear Transformation</span>
</h5>
<div class="statement"><p>Suppose that $\ltdefn{T}{U}{V}$ and $\ltdefn{S}{V}{W}$ are linear transformations.  Then $\ltdefn{(\compose{S}{T})}{U}{W}$ is a linear transformation.</p></div>
<div class="proof"><a knowl="./knowls/proof.CLTLT.knowl">Proof</a></div>
</div><div class="context"><a href="http://linear.pugetsound.edu/html/section-LT.html#theorem-CLTLT" class="context" title="Section LT">(in context)</a></div>
